sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Hook as traceability-scan.mjs
    participant AI as Command
    
    User->>Hook: /arckit:traceability PROJECT=001
    
    Note over Hook: Step 1: Scan Requirements
    Hook->>Hook: Read all ARC-*-REQ-*.md
    Hook->>Hook: Extract requirement IDs with regex
    Hook->>Hook: Parse categories, priorities, descriptions
    
    Note over Hook: Step 2: Scan Design Artifacts
    Hook->>Hook: Scan decisions/ for ARC-*-ADR-*
    Hook->>Hook: Scan vendors/*/ for HLD/DLD files
    Hook->>Hook: Scan for ARC-*-HLDR-*.md, ARC-*-DLDR-*.md
    Hook->>Hook: Extract all requirement ID references
    
    Note over Hook: Step 3: Compute Coverage
    Hook->>Hook: Match requirements to design references
    Hook->>Hook: Identify orphan requirements
    Hook->>Hook: Identify design-only references
    Hook->>Hook: Calculate coverage by category/priority
    
    Note over Hook: Step 4: Version Detection
    Hook->>Hook: Glob for existing ARC-*-TRAC-*.md
    Hook->>Hook: Extract latest version number
    Hook->>Hook: Suggest next version
    
    Hook-->>AI: Inject pre-extracted data<br/>Requirements table (70 rows)<br/>Coverage summary<br/>Orphan lists<br/>Version info
    
    AI->>AI: Format traceability report
    AI->>AI: Write ARC-001-TRAC-v1.1.md
